      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 2.5",
      "body" : "To avoid gluing word together (as discussed in comments to Kaleb&#39;s answer) the regex approach could be modified to <code>text.replaceAll(&quot;(\\\\r|\\\\n)+&quot;, &quot; &quot;)</code> and (assuming greedy is default in Java?) you will have a solution with just <i>one</i> space for each sequence of new line chars."
